modules.description: This module enables structured data manipulation through serialization, equality, hashing, and mapping operations on nested algebraic types with globalized fields, while efficiently transforming `option` and `result` types by zero-cost injection/removal of wrappers around values. It operates on `string list` collections, generic `'a Gel.t` containers, and mode-crossing data representations, supporting use cases like marshaling complex state across distributed systems or enforcing context-aware value scoping. The design emphasizes precise control over global/local value treatment during data transformation pipelines.
